      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DON ARTHUR (7) was responsible for a far better performance last start when successful over 2230m at this track, getting home by 4 metres after leading. Interesting to see what unfolds from this wide draw but this doesn't look as hard so it is a major player again. HEEZ A VIBE (6) turned in a much better run last time out, finishing runner-up over 2230m here after giving away a big start. This should be an easier assignment so he is a major player again. CLASSIC LINE (5) is worth another chance after a last-start eighth over 2190m at Mildura eight days ago. KATHYS FREE (3) was unplaced two starts ago then things went amiss last start when she copped a check and broke, finishing 35 metres away in fourth over 1800m at this course. A nice draw on the front line this time should ensure a cosy run. Finds a nice race and can make up for that last start mishap.",
